The '''Edo prison break''' was an attack on the federal maximum security prison at Oko in [[Benin City]],<ref>http://m.dailytimes.com.ng/article/edo-prison-break-police-prison-authorities-issue-conflicting-statements#.VIJHAMXgHa8</ref> the capital of [[Edo State]] in southern [[Nigeria]] by unknown gunmen suspected to be [[Robbery|Armed robbers]] in a bid to rescue their members who are largely condemn inmates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.informationng.com/2012/08/breaking-news-oko-federal-prison-in-benin-bombed-inmates-escaped.html|title=Breaking News – Oko Federal Prison In Benin Bombed, Inmates Escaped|author=Tolu|work=INFORMATION NIGERIA|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> About 12 prisoners escaped from the prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/12-inmates-escape-from-benin-city-prison/122772/ |title=12 Inmates Escape from Benin City Prison, Articles - THISDAY LIVE |publisher= |accessdate=27 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227164715/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/12-inmates-escape-from-benin-city-prison/122772/ |archivedate=27 December 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref>
==Incident== The incident occurred on Sunday 19 August 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2012/08/jail-break-police-beef-up-security-at-oko-prisons/|title=Jail break: Police beef up security at Oko Prisons|work=Vanguard News|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> It was reported than an explosive was used in the attack by the criminals to blown off the prison gate, a claim refuted by the Edo state commissioner of police, Olayinka Balogun.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelstv.com/2012/08/20/police-denys-use-of-bomb-in-benin-prison-break/|title=Police deny use of bomb in Benin prison break|work=Channels Television|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref> No death or severe injuries were recorded from the attack.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://saharareporters.com/2012/08/19/police-confirms-attempted-jail-break-edo-state-says-no-explosives-involved|title=Police Confirms Attempted Jail Break In Edo State, Says No "Explosives" Involved|work=Sahara Reporters|accessdate=27 December 2014}}</ref>
